summary: World No. 1 golfer Scottie Scheffler will miss the PGA Tour's season-opening tournament, The Sentry, due to a hand injury sustained while preparing Christmas dinner. The injury, a puncture wound, will require surgery and sideline Scheffler for 3-4 weeks. This unfortunate kitchen accident has derailed his scheduled 2023 start and forced him to withdraw from The Sentry, which was set to begin on January 5th. Scheffler is expected to return for The American Express, scheduled for January 19th-22nd.
